        "rationale": "This shaping focuses on power recovery in zone B as the weakest layer, with critical load restoration as primary success metric. It rewards power_B actions, MES deployment to B, and critical load recovery while penalizing excessive communication actions and premature feeder/coordinated operations. The state revision adds recovery ratios and progress metrics to guide decision-making.",
        "code": "from __future__ import annotations\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef revise_state(state, info=None):\n    \"\"\"Add recovery ratios and progress metrics to state representation\"\"\"\n    revised = list(state)\n    # Calculate recovery ratios for each layer\n    power_ratio = np.mean(state[0:3])  # Power zones A/B/C\n    comm_ratio = np.mean(state[3:6])   # Comm zones A/B/C\n    road_ratio = np.mean(state[6:9])   # Road zones A/B/C\n    # Critical load recovery progress\n    crit_load_ratio = np.mean(state[9:12])\n    # Add metrics to state (extend beyond original 24 dims conceptually)\n    revised.extend([power_ratio, comm_ratio, road_ratio, crit_load_ratio])\n    return np.array(revised)\n\ndef intrinsic_reward(state, action, next_state, info=None, revised_state=None):\n    \"\"\"Shape reward for critical load priority in middle stage\"\"\"\n    reward = 0.0\n    \n    # Critical load recovery reward (primary objective)\n    crit_load_improvement = np.sum(next_state[9:12]) - np.sum(state[9:12])\n    reward += 5.0 * crit_load_improvement\n    \n    # Power layer focus - zone B priority\n    if action == 4:  # power_B\n        reward += 2.0 * (next_state[1] - state[1])  # Zone B power improvement\n    \n    # MES deployment to zone B\n    if action == 10 and state[19] > 0.3:  # mes_to_B with sufficient SOC\n        reward += 1.5\n    \n    # Penalize excessive communication actions (especially non-B zones)\n    if action in [6, 8]:  # comm_A, comm_C\n        reward -= 1.0\n    if action in [7] and state[4] < 0.5:  # comm_B when power_B still low\n        reward -= 0.5\n    \n    # Discourage premature feeder/coordinated actions\n    backbone_power = state[12]\n    switching_cap = state[21]\n    if action in [12, 13]:  # feeder_reconfigure, coordinated_balanced\n        if backbone_power < 0.5 or switching_cap < 0.3:\n            reward -= 2.0\n    \n    # Balanced layer progress bonus\n    power_ratio = np.mean(state[0:3])\n    comm_ratio = np.mean(state[3:6])\n    if power_ratio < comm_ratio - 0.2:  # Power lagging behind comm\n        if action in [3, 4, 5]:  # Any power action\n            reward += 1.0\n    \n    return float(reward)",
